adders/ripple_carry/prompt1_adder_32.v
Prompt str:  //Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

endmodule

                     output wire cout,

  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);

endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;

  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

  wire [31:0] c;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c[0]);

endmodule

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;

  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], cout_temp[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], cout_temp[0]);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], cout, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);   
  wire [31:0] c;

  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], cout, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c[2]);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], c4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);

  adder_8 a8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], c7);
endmodule

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

                      output cout,

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);

endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,

//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;

  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], c4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);
  adder_8 a5(sum[39:32], c5, in1[39:32], in2[39:32], c4);
  adder_8 a6(sum[47:40], c6, in1[47:40], in2[47:40], c5);
  adder_8 a7(sum[55:48], c7, in1[55:48], in2[55:48], c6);
  adder_8 a8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);   
  wire [31:0] cout_temp;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], cout_temp[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], cout, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], cout, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], cout);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], cout, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], cout);
  adder_8 A4(sum[31:24], cout, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], cout);
  adder_8 A5(sum[39:32], cout, in1[39:32], in2[39:32], cout);
  adder_8 A6(sum[47:40], cout, in1[47:40], in2[47:40], cout);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], c4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);
  adder_8 a5(sum[39:32], c5, in1[39:32], in2[39:32], c4);
  adder_8 a6(sum[47:40], c6, in1[47:40], in2[47:40], c5);
  adder_8 a7(sum[55:48], c7, in1[55:48], in2[55:48], c6);
  adder_8 a8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], c7);
endmodule

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);

endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire cout1, cout2, cout3, cout4, cout5, cout6, cout7, cout8;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], cout1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], cout2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], cout1);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], cout3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], cout2);
  adder_8 A4(sum[31:24], cout4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], cout3);
  adder_8 A5(sum[39:32], cout5, in1[39:32], in2[39:32], cout4);

  adder_8 A8(sum[63:56], cout8, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], cout7);
  assign cout = cout8;
  assign sum = sum[63:0];
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], c4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);
  adder_8 a5(sum[39:32], c5, in1[39:32], in2[39:32], c4);
  adder_8 a6(sum[47:40], c6, in1[47:40], in2[47:40], c5);
  adder_8 a7(sum[55:48], c7, in1[55:48], in2[55:48], c6);
  adder_8 a8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  genvar i;
  generate
    for(i=0;i<32;i=i+1) begin
      adder_8 a8(sum[i+8*i],cout,in1[i+8*i],in2[i+8*i],cin);
    end
  endgenerate
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;

adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], c4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);
adder_8 a5(sum[39:32], c5, in1[39:32], in2[39:32], c4);
adder_8 a6(sum[47:40], c6, in1[47:40], in2[47:40], c5);
adder_8 a7(sum[55:48], c7, in1[55:48], in2[55:48], c6);
adder_8 a8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], c7);

endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire [31:0] c;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c[0]);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c[2], in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c[1]);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], cout, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c[2]);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire [7:0] c;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c[0]);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c[2], in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c[1]);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], c[3], in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c[2]);
  adder_8 a5(sum[39:32], c[4], in1[39:32], in2[39:32], c[3]);
  adder_8 a6(sum[47:40], c[5], in1[47:40], in2[47:40], c[4]);
  adder_8 a7(sum[55:48], c[6], in1[55:48], in2[55:48], c[5]);
  adder_8 a8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], c[6]);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire [31:0] carry;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], carry[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], carry[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], carry[0]);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], carry[2], in1[23:16], in2[23:16], carry[1]);
  adder_8 A4(sum[31:24], carry[3], in1[31:24], in2[31:24], carry[2]);
  adder_8 A5(sum[39:32], carry[4], in1[39:32], in2[39:32], carry[3]);
  adder_8 A6(sum[47:40], carry[5], in1[47:40], in2[47:40], carry[4]);
  adder_8 A7(sum[55:48], carry[6], in1[55:48], in2[55:48], carry[5]);
  adder_8 A8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], carry[6]);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire [31:0] c;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c[0]);

  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], cout, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c[2]);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire [31:0] cout_temp;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], cout_temp[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], cout_temp[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], cout_temp[0]);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], cout_temp[2], in1[23:16], in2[23:16], cout_temp[1]);
  adder_8 A4(sum[31:24], cout_temp[3], in1[31:24], in2[31:24], cout_temp[2]);
  adder_8 A5(sum[39:32], cout_temp[4], in1[39:32], in2[39:32], cout_temp[3]);
  adder_8 A6(sum[47:40], cout_temp[5], in1[47:40], in2[47:40], cout_temp[4]);
  adder_8 A7(sum[55:48], cout_temp[6], in1[55:48], in2[55:48], cout_temp[5]);
  adder_8 A8(sum[63:56], cout_temp[7], in1[63:56], in2[63:56], cout_temp[6]);
  assign cout = cout_temp[7];
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,

endmodule

//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], c4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);

endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  
  wire [31:0] c;
  wire [63:0] in1_64, in2_64;
  
  assign in1_64 = {in1[63:32], in1[31:0]};
  assign in2_64 = {in2[63:32], in2[31:0]};
  
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c[0], in1_64[7:0], in2_64[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c[1], in1_64[15:8], in2_64[15:8], c[0]);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c[2], in1_64[23:16], in2_64[23:16], c[1]);

endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

                      output cout,

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.

                     output wire cout,

  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
   wire [31:0] carry;
   adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], carry[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
   adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], carry[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], carry[0]);
   adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], carry[2], in1[23:16], in2[23:16], carry[1]);
   adder_8 A4(sum[31:24], carry[3], in1[31:24], in2[31:24], carry[2]);
   adder_8 A5(sum[39:32], carry[4], in1[39:32], in2[39:32], carry[3]);
   adder_8 A6(sum[47:40], carry[5], in1[47:40], in2[47:40], carry[4]);
   adder_8 A7(sum[55:48], carry[6], in1[55:48], in2[55:48], carry[5]);
   adder_8 A8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], carry[6]);
endmodule

//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
