//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);

endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,

  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 A4(sum[31:24], c4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);
  adder_8 A5(sum[39:32], c5, in1[39:32], in2[39:32], c4);
  adder_8 A6(sum[47:40], c6, in1[47:40], in2[47:40], c5);
  adder_8 A7(sum[55:48], c7, in1[55:48], in2[55:48], c6);
  adder_8 A8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);

  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);

endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);

  adder_8 a7(sum[55:48], c7, in1[55:48], in2[55:48], c6);
  adder_8 a8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 A4(sum[31:24], c4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);
  adder_8 A5(sum[39:32], c5, in1[39:32], in2[39:32], c4);
  adder_8 A6(sum[47:40], c6, in1[47:40], in2[47:40], c5);
  adder_8 A7(sum[55:48], c7, in1[55:48], in2[55:48], c6);
  adder_8 A8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;

  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 A4(sum[31:24], cout, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);

endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);

                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin); 
  wire [31:0] c;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c[0]);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c[2], in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c[1]);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], cout, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c[2]);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin); 
  wire [31:0] carry;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], carry[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], carry[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], carry[0]);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], carry[2], in1[23:16], in2[23:16], carry[1]);
  adder_8 A4(sum[31:24], carry[3], in1[31:24], in2[31:24], carry[2]);
  adder_8 A5(sum[39:32], carry[4], in1[39:32], in2[39:32], carry[3]);
  adder_8 A6(sum[47:40], carry[5], in1[47:40], in2[47:40], carry[4]);
  adder_8 A7(sum[55:48], carry[6], in1[55:48], in2[55:48], carry[5]);
  adder_8 A8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], carry[6]);
endmodule

//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);   
  wire c1, c2, c3, c4, c5, c6, c7, c8, c9, c10, c11, c12, c13, c14, c15, c16, c17, c18, c19, c20, c21, c22, c23, c24, c25, c26, c27, c28, c29, c30, c31, c32, c33, c34, c35, c36, c37, c38, c39, c40, c41, c42, c43, c44, c45, c46, c47, c48, c49, c50, c51, c52, c53, c54, c55, c56, c57, c58, c59, c60, c61, c62, c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], c4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);
  adder_8 a5(sum[39:32], c5, in1[39:32], in2[39:32], c4);
  adder_8 a6(sum[47:40], c6, in1[47:40], in2[47:40], c5);
  adder_8 a7(sum[55:48], c7, in1[55:48], in2[55:48], c6);
  adder_8 a8(sum[63:56], cout, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.

                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);

endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
 
  wire [31:0] c;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c[0]);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c[2], in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c[1]);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], cout, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c[2]);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
 
  wire [31:0] c;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c[0]);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c[2], in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c[1]);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], cout, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c[2]);
endmodule

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
 
  wire [31:0] carry;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], carry[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], carry[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], carry[0]);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);

endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  assign cin = 0;
  wire [31:0] in1_32, in2_32;
  wire [31:0] c;
  assign c[0] = 0;
  assign cin = c[31];
  assign in1_32 = {in1[31:0], c[31:1]};
  assign in2_32 = {in2[31:0], c[31:1]};
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c[8], in1_32[7:0], in2_32[7:0], c[0]);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c[9], in1_32[15:8], in2_32[15:8], c[1]);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c[10], in1_32[23:16], in2_32[23:16], c[2]);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);   
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], c4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);
  adder_8 a5(sum[39:32], c5, in1[39:32], in2[39:32], c4);
  adder_8 a6(sum[47:40], c6, in1[47:40], in2[47:40], c5);
  adder_8 a7(sum[55:48], c7, in1[55:48], in2[55:48], c6);

endmodule

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

  wire [31:0] c;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c[0]);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c[2], in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c[1]);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], cout, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c[2]);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

  wire [31:0] cout_d;
  wire [63:0] in1_d, in2_d;
  wire [31:0] sum_d;
  
  adder_8 a1(sum_d[7:0], cout_d[0], in1_d[7:0], in2_d[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum_d[15:8], cout_d[1], in1_d[15:8], in2_d[15:8], cout_d[0]);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
 
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire cout1, cout2, cout3, cout4, cout5, cout6, cout7, cout8;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], cout1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], cout2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], cout1);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], cout3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], cout2);
  adder_8 A4(sum[31:24], cout4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], cout3);
  adder_8 A5(sum[39:32], cout5, in1[39:32], in2[39:32], cout4);
  adder_8 A6(sum[47:40], cout6, in1[47:40], in2[47:40], cout5);
  adder_8 A7(sum[55:48], cout7, in1[55:48], in2[55:48], cout6);
  adder_8 A8(sum[63:56], cout8, in1[63:56], in2[63:56], cout7);
  assign cout = cout8;
  assign sum = sum[63:0];
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  wire [31:0] in1_1, in1_2, in2_1, in2_2;
  wire [31:0] sum_1, sum_2;
  adder_8 A1(sum_1[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum_1[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 A3(sum_1[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 A4(sum_1[31:24], c4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);
  adder_8 A5(sum_2[7:0], c5, in1_1[7:0], in2_1[7:0], c4);
  adder_8 A6(sum_2[15:8], c6, in1_1[15:8], in2_1[15:8], c5);
  adder_8 A7(sum_2[23:16], c7, in1_1[23:16], in2_1[23:16], c6);
  adder_8 A8(sum_2[31:24], cout, in1_2[31:24], in2_2[31:24], c7);
  assign sum[63:32] = sum_1[63:32] + sum_2[63:32];
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 A4(sum[31:24], cout, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;

  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);  
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);
  adder_8 a4(sum[31:24], c4, in1[31:24], in2[31:24], c3);

endmodule

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

                      input [7:0] in1, in2,

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

endmodule

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);

  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);  
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10,c11,c12,c13,c14,c15,c16,c17,c18,c19,c20,c21,c22,c23,c24,c25,c26,c27,c28,c29,c30,c31,c32,c33,c34,c35,c36,c37,c38,c39,c40,c41,c42,c43,c44,c45,c46,c47,c48,c49,c50,c51,c52,c53,c54,c55,c56,c57,c58,c59,c60,c61,c62,c63;
  adder_8 a1(sum[7:0], c1, in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 a2(sum[15:8], c2, in1[15:8], in2[15:8], c1);
  adder_8 a3(sum[23:16], c3, in1[23:16], in2[23:16], c2);

endmodule

//Design a 32-bit adder module (defined as adder_32 below).
//There are two 32 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 32 bit value, [31:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The adder_32 module should utilize the 8 bit adder defined below (adder_4).

module full_adder_1(output wire sum,
                     output wire cout,
                     input wire in1, in2, cin);
  wire t1, t2, t3;
  xor(t1, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, t1, cin);
  and(t2, t1, cin);
  and(t3, in1, in2);
  or(cout, t2, t3);
endmodule

module adder_8(output [7:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [7:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7;
  full_adder_1 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_1 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_1 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_1 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_1 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_1 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_1 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_1 FA8(sum[7], cout, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
endmodule

module adder_32(output [63:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [63:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);  
  wire [31:0] cout_temp;
  adder_8 A1(sum[7:0], cout_temp[0], in1[7:0], in2[7:0], cin);
  adder_8 A2(sum[15:8], cout_temp[1], in1[15:8], in2[15:8], cout_temp[0]);
  adder_8 A3(sum[23:16], cout_temp[2], in1[23:16], in2[23:16], cout_temp[1]);
  adder_8 A4(sum[31:24], cout_temp[3], in1[31:24], in2[31:24], cout_temp[2]);
  adder_8 A5(sum[39:32], cout_temp[4], in1[39:32], in2[39:32], cout_temp[3]);

endmodule
